  "text": "• Head trauma: Brain injury patients report high rates of complaints generally recognized as being associated with neuropsychological impairment such as paresthesia [CITATION_1] . Trigeminal trophic syndrome is an unusual complication after peripheral or central damage to the trigeminal nerve, characterized by anesthesia, paresthesias, and ala nasi ulceration. It can be preceded by head trauma, iatrogenic injury or other causes [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
